<subSubSection pageId="98" pageNumber="99" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="98.[151,1437,152,487]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,567,268,294]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
From 1°55’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[728,817,268,294]" degrees="8" direction="north" minutes="34" orientation="latitude" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" precision="925" value="8.566667">8°34’N</geoCoordinate>
and 57°52’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[994,1102,268,294]" degrees="62" direction="west" minutes="55" orientation="longitude" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" precision="925" value="-62.916668">62°55’W</geoCoordinate>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1165,1256,268,294]" name="Guyana" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Guyana</collectingCountry>
and adjacent 
<collectingCountry box="[151,275,306,332]" name="Venezuela" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[336,410,306,332]" name="Brazil" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Brazil</collectingCountry>
at 337(35–900) m elevation in lowland rainforest in a variety of habitats, including flooded and non-flooded areas (
<figureCitation box="[524,612,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="97.[151,256,1733,1756]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,689,1697]" captionTargetId="figure@97.[151,1436,666,1714]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURE 25. Distribution maps of Geonoma maxima subsp. maxima, G. maxima subsp. ambigua, G. maxima subsp. camptoneura, and G. maxima subsp. chelidonura." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3538412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3538412/files/figure.png" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="98.[151,1437,152,487]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
A specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[412,503,384,410]" name="Guyana" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Guyana</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[521,710,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">McDowell 4479</emphasis>
) has more pinnae than others and approaches 
<taxonomicName box="[1261,1436,384,410]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="maxima" subSpecies="maxima">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1343,1436,385,410]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its leaf morphology. Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Spruce" box="[543,727,422,448]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="maxima" subSpecies="ambigua">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[624,727,422,448]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has fewer pinnae per side of the rachis than subsp. m 
<emphasis box="[1357,1429,424,449]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">axima</emphasis>
, it usually has a few, 1-veined pinnae present.
</paragraph>
